  <item nodeId="node-643">
    <command xml:space="preserve">2</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">[Wax poetical a bit.]&#x000A;&#x000A;"I have read and felt what it was like to thunder across the plains as a gazelle from the scroll of izyuk.  I have read and felt the desperate yen of attraction from the scroll of obidil. From the scroll you now hold in your posession, I have read and felt what it is to be the very earth itself, spinning through the cosmos."&#x000A;&#x000A;Constance looks at you.  A beat.  "So you don't know."&#x000A;&#x000A;"I don't know," you agree.&#x000A;&#x000A;Constance waits.  OK, you can give her this one.&#x000A;&#x000A;"I don't know because reading is my heritage, as the ability to summon mist is yours.  But understanding is not part of that gift."&#x000A;&#x000A;"Well that sucks," Constance says.&#x000A;&#x000A;"It is a touch of the language of the gods," you say, simply.  "It is enough."&#x000A;&#x000A;The two of you make another circuit.  The mist streams off the ends of your outstretched wings in curled eddies.&#x000A;&#x000A;"So, you want to read a capsa's scroll.  And you won't know what you're reading." says Constance, after a bit.&#x000A;&#x000A;1) Share your speculation.&#x000A;2) OK, I'm a tester and I need to go back and check Constance fiddling with scrolls and stuff.&#x000A;3) I'm also a tester, and I just want to go back to the beginning of this conversation.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-644"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-644">
    <command xml:space="preserve">1</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">[Share your speculation.]&#x000A;&#x000A;"I will not know what it is I'm saying, but I have a guess about what will happen.&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;&#x000A;And no capsae holder I have yet met will risk such a thing," you say.&#x000A;&#x000A;Constance scoffs.  "No Queen or King, you mean.&#x000A;&#x000A;"You personally currently hold three capsae, more than some kingdoms."&#x000A;&#x000A;Constance laughs.  "'Cause I stole 'em!  And they weren't even the one I wanted; I just didn't know what color I was after&#x000A;&#x000A;1) OK, I'm a tester and I need to go back and check Constance fiddling with scrolls and stuff.&#x000A;2) I'm also a tester, and I just want to go back to the beginning of this conversation.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-645"/>
    </children>
  </item>
