      <child nodeId="node-1011"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-1011">
    <command xml:space="preserve">e</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">Librum Landing Cradle&#x000A;The Landing Cradle of the Librum is beautifully set with interlocking redwood and pine, suggesting shelves of books.  The Librum Door leads inward to the Librum itself.&#x000A;&#x000A;To the west is the Great Hall, and to the northwest is the Royal Quarters and Gardens.  You can also re-ascend to the skies or descend to the forest below.&#x000A;&#x000A;Horatio is talking slowly to the lone guard about the ethics of a monarchy, driving the guard quietly insane.&#x000A;&#x000A;In the cradle next to the guard is a small pile of tiny padlocks, each open.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-1012"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-1012">
    <command xml:space="preserve">close purple</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">You close the purple capsa of opening.&#x000A;&#x000A;You feel your skin prickle where you were wounded, and look down.  To your amazement, your wound has closed and the bleeding stopped.  As you watch, even the line from the cut disappears, and the feathers around it fluff out again.&#x000A;&#x000A;It's the scroll of Health.  It has to be.  It's actually here!  And active.  Hmm.&#x000A;&#x000A;The guard closes the Librum door.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-1013"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-1013">
    <command xml:space="preserve">open purple</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">You open the purple capsa of opening, revealing a scroll of rezrov.&#x000A;&#x000A;As you open the purple capsa, an almost-palpable wave of force emanates from it, as the power of the revealed scroll of rezrov is released.&#x000A;&#x000A;The magic of the gold capsa of down prevents it from being opened.&#x000A;The magic of the red capsa of hasten prevents it from being opened.&#x000A;Librum Door flies open!&#x000A;The magic of the blue capsa of mist prevents it from being opened.&#x000A;&#x000A;From... well, from everywhere in the Aerie, it seems, Woodpeckers start drumming out messages in their Pounding dialect:  "Intruder! Estimated direction is..." and then each one individually seems to be telegraphing the direction from them to you.  You can't discern any one drummer from any other drummer, but you can at least tell that each seems to be drumming on sheets of metal that differ from each other, as the frequencies are all different from each other.  That makes the information somewhat useless to you, because you've not been trained to distinguish Pounding at different frequencies.  And because you already know where you are.  Sadly, the Raven Guards are indeed trained to distinguish Pounding frequencies.&#x000A;&#x000A;And if they didn't know where you were, they do now.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-1014"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-1014">
    <command xml:space="preserve">l</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">Librum Landing Cradle&#x000A;The Landing Cradle of the Librum is beautifully set with interlocking redwood and pine, suggesting shelves of books.  The Librum Door leads inward to the Librum itself.&#x000A;&#x000A;To the west is the Great Hall, and to the northwest is the Royal Quarters and Gardens.  You can also re-ascend to the skies or descend to the forest below.&#x000A;&#x000A;Horatio is talking slowly to the lone guard about his grandchildren, driving the guard quietly insane.&#x000A;&#x000A;In the cradle next to the guard is a small pile of tiny padlocks, each open.&#x000A;&#x000A;A squad of Raven Guards appears, and their war cries exalt as they spot you.  You weave through the air, tumbling and twisting as you try to avoid them.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-871">
    <command xml:space="preserve">e</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">You tuck in your wings and dive down east towards the Aerie, thrilling to the misty wind streaming through your feathers.&#x000A;&#x000A;Librum Landing Cradle&#x000A;The Landing Cradle of the Librum is beautifully set with interlocking redwood and pine, suggesting shelves of books.  The Librum Door leads inward to the Librum itself.&#x000A;&#x000A;To the west is the Great Hall, and to the northwest is the Royal Quarters and Gardens.  You can also re-ascend to the skies or descend to the forest below.&#x000A;&#x000A;Horatio is talking slowly to the lone guard about the ethics of a monarchy, driving the guard quietly insane.&#x000A;&#x000A;In the cradle next to the guard is a small pile of tiny padlocks, each open.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve">You tuck in your wings and dive down towards the Aerie, thrilling to the misty wind streaming through your feathers.&#x000A;&#x000A;Librum Landing Cradle&#x000A;The Landing Cradle of the Librum is beautifully set with interlocking redwood and pine, suggesting shelves of books.  The Librum Door leads inward to the Librum itself.&#x000A;&#x000A;To the west is the Great Hall, and to the northwest is the Royal Quarters and Gardens.  You can also re-ascend to the skies or descend to the forest below.&#x000A;&#x000A;Horatio is talking slowly to the lone guard about the ethics of a monarchy, driving the guard quietly insane.&#x000A;&#x000A;In the cradle next to the guard is a small pile of tiny padlocks, each open.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
