    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-875">
    <command xml:space="preserve">out</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">Listening to Horatio talk with the guard, you enter the shadows just inside the Librum door, where you can watch the guard but not be seen.  When the moment is right, you launch yourself through, and back up into the safety of the mist.&#x000A;&#x000A;Librum Landing Cradle&#x000A;The Landing Cradle of the Librum is beautifully set with interlocking redwood and pine, suggesting shelves of books.  The Librum Door leads inward to the Librum itself.&#x000A;&#x000A;To the west is the Great Hall, and to the northwest is the Royal Quarters and Gardens.  You can also re-ascend to the skies or descend to the forest below.&#x000A;&#x000A;Horatio is talking quickly to the lone guard about his grandchildren, driving the guard quietly insane.&#x000A;&#x000A;In the cradle next to the guard is a small pile of tiny padlocks, each open.&#x000A;&#x000A;Your wound continues to bleed.  It's not a huge wound, but the blood is flowing rather quickly.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve">Listening to Horatio talk with the guard, you enter the shadows just inside the Librum door, where you can watch the guard but not be seen.  When the moment is right, you launch yourself through, and back up into the safety of the mist.&#x000A;&#x000A;Librum Landing Cradle&#x000A;The Landing Cradle of the Librum is beautifully set with interlocking redwood and pine, suggesting shelves of books.  The Librum Door leads inward to the Librum itself.&#x000A;&#x000A;To the west is the Great Hall, and to the northwest is the Royal Quarters and Gardens.  You can also re-ascend to the skies or descend to the forest below.&#x000A;&#x000A;Horatio is talking quickly to the lone guard about his grandchildren, driving the guard quietly insane.&#x000A;&#x000A;In the cradle next to the guard is a small pile of tiny padlocks, each open.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-876"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-876">
    <command xml:space="preserve">w</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">Great Hall Landing Cradle&#x000A;The Landing Cradle of the Great Hall spreads out over nearly a quarter of the vast building.  During your time here, you learned this was so that when a number of important guests and their retinues arrive at the same time, they can land simultaneously, instead of one after the other, which some would invariably take as meaning "in order of importance".  The huge double doors of the Great Hall are on the west side of the landing cradle, and unguarded.&#x000A;&#x000A;To the north is the Royal Quarters and Gardens, the Librum to the east, and as always, you can return to the skies or descend to the forest.&#x000A;&#x000A;Horatio glides out of the mist and circles near you.  He nods at the black capsa.  "Excellent work.  Now, we need something from the Great Hall."&#x000A;&#x000A;Horatio glides through the open double doors of the Great Hall.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve">Great Hall Landing Cradle&#x000A;The Landing Cradle of the Great Hall spreads out over nearly a quarter of the vast building.  During your time here, you learned this was so that when a number of important guests and their retinues arrive at the same time, they can land simultaneously, instead of one after the other, which some would invariably take as meaning "in order of importance".  The huge double doors of the Great Hall are on the west side of the landing cradle, and unguarded.&#x000A;&#x000A;To the north is the Royal Quarters and Gardens, the Librum to the east, and as always, you can return to the skies or descend to the forest.&#x000A;&#x000A;Your wound continues to bleed.  It's not a huge wound, but the blood is flowing rather quickly.&#x000A;&#x000A;Horatio glides out of the mist and circles near you.  He nods at the black capsa.  "Excellent work.  Now, we need something from the Great Hall."&#x000A;&#x000A;Horatio glides through the open double doors of the Great Hall.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</commentary>
