      <child nodeId="node-882"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-895">
    <command xml:space="preserve">close black</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">(the black capsa)&#x000A;You close the black capsa.&#x000A;&#x000A;The hunting cloaks appear again.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve">(the black capsa)&#x000A;You close the black capsa.&#x000A;&#x000A;The hunting cloaks appear again.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-896"/>
      <child nodeId="node-1080"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-896">
    <command xml:space="preserve">get cloaks</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">You reach out and pick up the cloak.  It seems none the worse for wear from having been invisible.  Next to you, Horatio picks up the other.&#x000A;&#x000A;You turn to Horatio, questions bubbling in your head.  "So, nothing else here turned invisible.  Does the scroll work on cloaks?  Things for hunting?  Ancient materials?  Hides?"&#x000A;&#x000A;Horatio looks a little uncomfortable.  "No.  It works on... purple."&#x000A;&#x000A;"Purple?!?" you exclaim/ask.&#x000A;&#x000A;"Purple," he confirms.&#x000A;&#x000A;"It turns purple things invisible?  Purple things!  The gift from the gods, on a scroll written in their secret language!  To turn purple things invisible!"  You cackle in glee.&#x000A;&#x000A;Horatio looks uncomfortably affronted.  "The hippotomai were common in those days.  It made sense..."&#x000A;&#x000A;You continue to laugh, cutting him off, but unable to contain your utter delight.  "Herds of invisible hippotomai!  Grass on the marshy banks disappearing into nowhere!  Weird divots in the lakes!  I bet--wait!  The trickster god!  Ape, the trickster!  Stohleblanc!"  You laughter gets more hysterical and you nearly can't breathe.&#x000A;&#x000A;With as much dignity as he can muster, Horatio waits solemnly for you to finish laughing.  You fail to do so.  Finally he gets impatient and turns to go.  "We can enter the Royal Quarters cloaked.  I will follow you."&#x000A;&#x000A;"Wait," you sputter, trying to push down the hysteria.  "How will you follow me?  I'll be invisible!"&#x000A;&#x000A;"I can sense the capsae.  I will know where you are," he replies, and with a deep breath, he gathers himself and flies up and out of the Great Hall.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve">That's fixed in place.&#x000A;&#x000A;Your wound aches.  You look down at it, and it's still open and a fast small trickle of blood drips down your side.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-897"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-897">
    <command xml:space="preserve">get cloak</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">(the purple hunting cloak)&#x000A;You already have that.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve">(the purple hunting cloak)&#x000A;You reach out and pick up the cloak.  It seems none the worse for wear from having been invisible.  Next to you, Horatio picks up the other.&#x000A;&#x000A;You turn to Horatio, questions bubbling in your head.  "So, nothing else here turned invisible.  Does the scroll work on cloaks?  Things for hunting?  Ancient materials?  Hides?"&#x000A;&#x000A;Horatio looks a little uncomfortable.  "No.  It works on... purple."&#x000A;&#x000A;"Purple?!?" you exclaim/ask.&#x000A;&#x000A;"Purple," he confirms.&#x000A;&#x000A;"It turns purple things invisible?  Purple things!  The gift from the gods, on a scroll written in their secret language!  To turn purple things invisible!"  You cackle in glee.&#x000A;&#x000A;Horatio looks uncomfortably affronted.  "The hippotomai were common in those days.  It made sense..."&#x000A;&#x000A;You continue to laugh, cutting him off, but unable to contain your utter delight.  "Herds of invisible hippotomai!  Grass on the marshy banks disappearing into nowhere!  Weird divots in the lakes!  I bet--wait!  The trickster god!  Ape, the trickster!  Stohleblanc!"  You laughter gets more hysterical and you nearly can't breathe.&#x000A;&#x000A;With as much dignity as he can muster, Horatio waits solemnly for you to finish laughing.  You fail to do so.  Finally he gets impatient and turns to go.  "We can enter the Royal Quarters cloaked.  I will follow you."&#x000A;&#x000A;"Wait," you sputter, trying to push down the hysteria.  "How will you follow me?  I'll be invisible!"&#x000A;&#x000A;"I can sense the capsae.  I will know where you are," he replies, and with a deep breath, he gathers himself and flies up and out of the Great Hall.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-898"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-898">
    <command xml:space="preserve">i</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">You are carrying:&#x000A;  a purple hunting cloak&#x000A;  a black capsa (closed)&#x000A;  a leather rucksack (open)&#x000A;    a blue capsa of mist (closed)&#x000A;    a red capsa of hasten (open)&#x000A;      a scroll of quiste&#x000A;    a purple capsa of opening (open)&#x000A;      a scroll of rezrov&#x000A;    a gold capsa of down (closed)&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve">You are carrying:&#x000A;  a purple hunting cloak&#x000A;  a black capsa (closed)&#x000A;  a leather rucksack (open)&#x000A;    a blue capsa of mist (closed)&#x000A;    a red capsa of hasten (open)&#x000A;      a scroll of quiste&#x000A;    a purple capsa of opening (open)&#x000A;      a scroll of rezrov&#x000A;    a gold capsa of down (closed)&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-899"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-899">
    <command xml:space="preserve">x cloak</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">(the purple hunting cloak)&#x000A;In prehistoric times, people made these cloaks out of hippotomai skins to mask their scent.  The dark purple variegation also helped with camoflage.  You couldn't fly with them on, but some prey had gotten extremely adept and spotting flying enemies, so hunters took to sneaking up on foot.  On foot!&#x000A;.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve">(the purple hunting cloak)&#x000A;In prehistoric times, people made these cloaks out of hippotomai skins to mask their scent.  The dark purple variegation also helped with camoflage.  You couldn't fly with them on, but some prey had gotten extremely adept and spotting flying enemies, so hunters took to sneaking up on foot.  On foot!&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-900"/>
    </children>
  </item>
